<br>
The off-hand is totally independant of the main-hand.<br>
<br>
Take for instance:<br>
<br>
Main Hand: Paw of Opolla [or any other non-weapon type item]<br>
Off-Hand: Rusty Short Sword [or any other Off-hand equippable weapon]<br>
<br>
Now based on your theory, the Off-hand shouldn't swing right? Cos the Main-Hand doesn't swing, or have any delay factor, thus the check for dual-wield would never happen?<br>
<br>
But in the above setup, the Off-hand DOES swing. So in actual fact, everytime the delay of the OFF-hand is up, a check on dual-wield is done. Thus:<br>
<br>
;<br>
01 Check Weapon Delay<br>
02 If Weapon Delay &gt;0 then goto 01 [ie. Weapon delay not ready yet]<br>
03 If Weapon Delay =0 then goto 04 [Weapon delay is up, and ready to swing]<br>
04 Roll Dual Wield<br>
05 Check Dual Wield<br>
06 If Dual Wield = 0 then goto 01 [0 = fail, thus recheck on next delay]<br>
07 If Dual Wield = 1 then goto 08 [1 = succes, now check for Double Attack]<br>
08 Roll Double Attack<br>
09 If Double Attack = 0 then goto 11 [0 = fail, thus Swing 1 time]<br>
